South Korea’s most effective weapon against the virus has been to rapidly expand testing.
South Korea’s testing, of course, caused a spike in confirmed cases, which number 7,513 as of Tuesday.
ADADThe number of daily confirmed cases has been steadily declining, from 686 on March 2 to just 131 on Tuesday, according to government figures.
South Korea’s civil society has voluntarily pitched in.
ADSome of South Korea’s measures have been controversial.